<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="93" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,692,680,707]" box="[189,692,680,707]" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,692,680,707]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="93" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,692,680,707]" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">
Diagnosis of the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[395,596,680,707]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[395,596,680,707]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Merodon aureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lineage
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,728,825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">
Mid coxa with long pile posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[632,728,728,754]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1877,1903]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,653,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-157@6.[189,1398,653,1842]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. A–C. Merodon funestus (Fabricius, 1794), ♂. A. Mid coxa (FSUNS; FSUNS ID F98), lateral view, posterior pile marked with arrow. B. Anterior anepisternum (CWM; FSUNS ID 10347), pile below postpronotum marked with arrow, anterolateral view. C. Abdomen, dorsal view (FSUNS; FSUNS ID F99). Scale bar = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013006/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
); anterior anepisternum below postpronotum with many long pile (
<figureCitation box="[309,402,763,789]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1877,1903]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,653,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-157@6.[189,1398,653,1842]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. A–C. Merodon funestus (Fabricius, 1794), ♂. A. Mid coxa (FSUNS; FSUNS ID F98), lateral view, posterior pile marked with arrow. B. Anterior anepisternum (CWM; FSUNS ID 10347), pile below postpronotum marked with arrow, anterolateral view. C. Abdomen, dorsal view (FSUNS; FSUNS ID F99). Scale bar = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013006/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
); species with stocky abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[785,878,763,789]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1877,1903]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,653,1839]" captionTargetId="figure-157@6.[189,1398,653,1842]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. A–C. Merodon funestus (Fabricius, 1794), ♂. A. Mid coxa (FSUNS; FSUNS ID F98), lateral view, posterior pile marked with arrow. B. Anterior anepisternum (CWM; FSUNS ID 10347), pile below postpronotum marked with arrow, anterolateral view. C. Abdomen, dorsal view (FSUNS; FSUNS ID F99). Scale bar = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013006/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
); lateral sclerites of the aedeagus very small or absent (
<figureCitation box="[312,407,799,825]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[210,1307,1074,1791]" captionTargetId="figure-255@7.[189,1398,1055,1811]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Male genitalia, aedeagus, lateral view. A. Merodon aureus (Fabricius, 1805) (FSUNS; FSUNS ID 09662) the place of absence of lateral sclerite of the aedeagus marked with arrow. B. M. funestus (Fabricius, 1794) (FSUNS; FSUNS ID F99). C. M. bombiformis Hull, 1944 (FSUNS; FSUNS ID A2_079). D. M. zebraVujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov., paratype (BMNH; FSUNS ID 03314).Abbreviations: ea = ejaculatory apodeme; p = aedeagus; s = lateral sclerite of aedeagus. Scale bar = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013010" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013010/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
: marked with arrow).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,750,864,891]" box="[189,750,864,891]" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,750,864,891]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="5" pageNumber="93" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,750,864,891]" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">
Diagnosis of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1944" box="[397,668,864,891]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombiformis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[397,668,864,891]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Merodon bombiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,911,1080]" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">
Pedicel elongated, approximately as long as basoflagellomere (
<figureCitation box="[981,1061,911,937]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[231,1357,265,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[231,1357,265,1811]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Male antenna, lateral view. A. Merodon bombiformis Hull, 1944 (FSUNS; FSUNS ID ZA2_079). B. M. multifasciatus Curran, 1939 (USNM; FSUNS ID 04512). C. M. vittatus Vujić &amp; Likov sp. nov., holotype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 04085). D. M. zebra Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov. paratype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 05174). E. M. lotus Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov., paratype (FSUNS; FSUNS ID ZA6_066). F. M. nasicus Bezzi, 1915 (TAUI; FSUNS ID 04972). Scale bar = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013014" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013014/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); abdomen broad (
<figureCitation box="[1303,1382,911,938]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[313,1211,287,1733]" captionTargetId="figure-11@10.[274,1312,287,1814]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. Male abdomen, dorsal view. A. Merodon bombiformis Hull, 1944 (FSUNS; FSUNS ZA2_079). B. M. multifasciatus Curran, 1939 (USNM 2052372; FSUNS ID 04512). C. M. vittatus Vujić &amp; Likov sp. nov. holotype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 04085). D. M. zebra Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov. holotype (RMCA; FSUNS ID 25089). E. M. lotus Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov., paratype (FSUNS; FSUNS ID ZA6_066). F. M. nasicus Bezzi, 1915 (RBINS; FSUNS ID 21976). Scale bar = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013018" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013018/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); metafemur with less serrated apicoventral triangular lamina, usually only the apical dens is distinct (
<figureCitation box="[198,270,982,1009]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[199,1398,311,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-11@12.[189,1398,311,1769]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Male metaleg, lateral view. A. Merodon bombiformis Hull, 1944 (FSUNS; FSUNS ZA2_079). B. M. multifasciatus Curran, 1939 (USNM 2052372; FSUNS ID 04512). C. M. vittatus Vujić &amp; Likov sp. nov., holotype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 04085). D. M. zebra Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov., paratype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 05174). E. M. lotus Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov., paratype (FSUNS; FSUNS ID ZA6_066). F. M. nasicus Bezzi, 1915 (TAUI; FSUNS ID 04972). Scale bar = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013020/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); metatrochanter of males smooth, without calcar (
<figureCitation box="[868,940,982,1009]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[189,232,1852,1878]" captionTargetBox="[199,1398,311,1740]" captionTargetId="figure-11@12.[189,1398,311,1769]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Male metaleg, lateral view. A. Merodon bombiformis Hull, 1944 (FSUNS; FSUNS ZA2_079). B. M. multifasciatus Curran, 1939 (USNM 2052372; FSUNS ID 04512). C. M. vittatus Vujić &amp; Likov sp. nov., holotype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 04085). D. M. zebra Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov., paratype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 05174). E. M. lotus Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov., paratype (FSUNS; FSUNS ID ZA6_066). F. M. nasicus Bezzi, 1915 (TAUI; FSUNS ID 04972). Scale bar = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013020" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013020/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); male genitalia with posterior surstyle lobe usually bent (as on 
<figureCitation box="[469,596,1017,1044]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1882,1908]" captionTargetBox="[203,1381,605,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-111@13.[189,1398,579,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 7. Male genitalia. A–C. Merodon zebra Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov., paratype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 05174). D–F. M. vittatus Vujić &amp; Likov sp. nov., holotype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 04085). A, D. Epandrium, lateral view. B, E. Epandrium, ventral view. C, F. Hypandrium, lateral view. Abbreviations: ams = anterior margin of surstyle; c = cercus; pl = posterior lobe of surstyle. Scale bar = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013022/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 7A, D</figureCitation>
: pl), and hypandrium narrowed medially (as on 
<figureCitation box="[1151,1241,1017,1044]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="13.[189,232,1882,1908]" captionTargetBox="[203,1381,605,1792]" captionTargetId="figure-111@13.[189,1398,579,1845]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="Fig. 7. Male genitalia. A–C. Merodon zebra Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov., paratype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 05174). D–F. M. vittatus Vujić &amp; Likov sp. nov., holotype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 04085). A, D. Epandrium, lateral view. B, E. Epandrium, ventral view. C, F. Hypandrium, lateral view. Abbreviations: ams = anterior margin of surstyle; c = cercus; pl = posterior lobe of surstyle. Scale bar = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013022" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013022/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
: marked with arrow); distribution: Afrotropical Region (
<figureCitation box="[685,754,1053,1079]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[189,232,1990,2016]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,1302,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-245@3.[189,1398,1302,1949]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 1. Distribution map of the Merodon bombiformis species group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013002" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013002/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[189,1399,1119,1429]" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">
The 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1944" box="[247,515,1119,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bombiformis">
<emphasis box="[247,515,1119,1145]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Merodon bombiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Fabricius, 1794)" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[664,1025,1119,1145]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funestus">
<emphasis box="[664,805,1119,1145]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">M. funestus</emphasis>
(Fabricius, 1794)
</taxonomicName>
differ from other species and groups among the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1805" box="[413,492,1155,1180]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Merodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aureus">
<emphasis box="[413,492,1155,1180]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">aureus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
lineage by an elongated pedicel, approximately as long or even longer than basoflagellomere (
<figureCitation box="[411,484,1190,1216]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="8.[189,232,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[231,1357,265,1811]" captionTargetId="figure-11@8.[231,1357,265,1811]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Fig. 4. Male antenna, lateral view. A. Merodon bombiformis Hull, 1944 (FSUNS; FSUNS ID ZA2_079). B. M. multifasciatus Curran, 1939 (USNM; FSUNS ID 04512). C. M. vittatus Vujić &amp; Likov sp. nov., holotype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 04085). D. M. zebra Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov. paratype (NBCN; FSUNS ID 05174). E. M. lotus Vujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov., paratype (FSUNS; FSUNS ID ZA6_066). F. M. nasicus Bezzi, 1915 (TAUI; FSUNS ID 04972). Scale bar = 2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013014" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013014/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
) and small lateral sclerite of the aedeagus (as on 
<figureCitation box="[1097,1232,1190,1216]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[189,232,1848,1874]" captionTargetBox="[210,1307,1074,1791]" captionTargetId="figure-255@7.[189,1398,1055,1811]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 3. Male genitalia, aedeagus, lateral view. A. Merodon aureus (Fabricius, 1805) (FSUNS; FSUNS ID 09662) the place of absence of lateral sclerite of the aedeagus marked with arrow. B. M. funestus (Fabricius, 1794) (FSUNS; FSUNS ID F99). C. M. bombiformis Hull, 1944 (FSUNS; FSUNS ID A2_079). D. M. zebraVujić &amp; Radenković sp. nov., paratype (BMNH; FSUNS ID 03314).Abbreviations: ea = ejaculatory apodeme; p = aedeagus; s = lateral sclerite of aedeagus. Scale bar = 0.25 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5013010" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5013010/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="93">Fig. 3B, D</figureCitation>
